<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="shelter-v">shelter <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /'ʃeltə(r)/    美 /'ʃeltər/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-vt">1.★ <strong>vt 掩蔽；保护；为...提供避难所：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The darkness of the night sheltered their activities.
黑夜掩护了他们的行动。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>shelter ... from :</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Trees were planted to shelter this area from strong sand storms.
人们种树使这个地区免受强沙尘暴的侵袭。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-vi">2.★ <strong>vi 躲避；避难：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We sat in the shade, <strong>sheltering from</strong> the sun.
我们坐在背阴处躲避日晒。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Some parents are just too protective. They want to shelter their kids  <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ every kind of danger, real or imagined.  （2009 湖北改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. from  </p></div>